        <h3>"Compactor completely dead — nothing happens when I press Start"</h3>
        <p>Failed door safety switch on a KitchenAid built-in trash compactor installed in a 2004 kitchen remodel in Brentwood. The homeowner had checked the key switch position and circuit breaker — both correct — but the unit remained completely unresponsive. The door safety switch, which must detect the drawer is fully closed before allowing the motor circuit to complete, had failed open, cutting power to the entire start sequence.</p>
        <div class="repair-detail">Confirmed door switch failure with continuity test — open circuit in closed position. Replaced door safety switch with OEM KitchenAid part. Unit started normally on first attempt after replacement. Tested through five complete compaction cycles. Also checked drive gear condition — found early wear on the first stage gear teeth, advised homeowner it would need replacement within 12–18 months. They declined at this visit. Total repair: $155.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-card">
        <div class="repair-title">Pasadena · Home · Whirlpool GC900QPPB Freestanding</div>
        <h3>"Loud grinding sound — it tries to run but makes horrible noise"</h3>
        <p>Stripped drive gear on a Whirlpool freestanding trash compactor. The main drive gear — a nylon gear that transfers motor torque to the ram drive mechanism — had stripped approximately 40% of its teeth. The motor was running, the sound was the remaining intact teeth engaging intermittently and the stripped section causing the grinding when it cycled through. The compactor had been making a mild sound for several months before it escalated to grinding, which is the typical progression of drive gear wear.</p>
        <div class="repair-detail">Replaced Whirlpool drive gear assembly with OEM replacement. Verified full compaction force through three cycles with a weight load — ram descending to full compression without slipping. Also replaced the drive chain which showed stretch beyond specification — on these models the chain and gear should be replaced together when either fails. Total repair: $210.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
